A man, believed to be in his 50s, was killed when his motorbike crashed into a barrier on the R102 near Grootbrak River in the Western Cape on Sunday afternoon, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics, along with Metro Services, arrived on the scene to find the the bike on the side of the road. The biker was found a few feet away, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene. The girlfriend of the deceased later told paramedics that the man lost control of the motorbike, causing it to crash into the barrier, Meiring said.